# PostPilot Client

## Stack

React 19 · Vite 8 · TypeScript · React Router 7 · Redux Toolkit + RTK Query · React Hook Form · Zod · shadcn/ui · Tailwind 4 · Sonner

UI kit: `docs/designSystem.md`

## API calls

- Dev: relative `/api/...` (Vite proxy → `:3000`)
- Always `credentials: 'include'` for cookie auth
- RTK Query in `store/api/` for server state; auth in `store/auth.slice.ts`
- Legacy fetch wrappers in `utils/` — migrate to `entities/*/api/` over time

## FSD layers (target, after M6)

Migrating gradually. **New code after M6** should follow FSD minimum:

```
client/src/
  app/        # providers, router
  pages/      # route screens only
  widgets/    # composite blocks (sidebar, landing sections)
  features/   # user actions (createPost, publishPost, connectChannel)
  entities/   # domain types + API (post, channel, user)
  shared/     # ui/, lib/, config/
```

### Import rules (strict)

| Layer | May import from |
|-------|-----------------|
| `app` | all layers |
| `pages` | widgets, features, entities, shared |
| `widgets` | features, entities, shared |
| `features` | entities, shared |
| `entities` | shared only |
| `shared` | nothing above |

Legacy code in `pages/`, `components/`, `store/`, `utils/` is OK until migrated.

## Conventions

- Functional components; small and focused
- No `any`; explicit API response types
- shadcn components in `components/ui/` (→ `shared/ui/` when migrated)
- Scope Pre-MVP: SPA after login, one channel, text posts, publish now
